    <title>Grandmas Punch</title>

    <comment></comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>
    



    <ingredient>2L Pineapple juice</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1.25L Lemonade</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1.5L Cranberry juice</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 cans 440 gms Pineapple pieces in juice</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 punets strawberries washed and chopped</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 bunch mint washed and chopped</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 Lime finely sliced</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 1/2 cups Vodka (optional)</ingredient>

    <step>Place all items in fridge over night except ice (leave this in freezer.)</step>
    <step>Place all items in a large punch bowl and stir well. Add as much ice as desired (4-5 handfuls.)</step>
</recipe>